NAME
lxcu-upgrade.sh -- Upgrade an lxc container of a certain type.
SYNOPSIS
lxcu-upgrade.sh [OPTIONS]
DESCRIPTION
lxcu-upgrade.sh will upgrade a container of a certain type for a specified
distribution and release. If a type other than basic is specified, 'basic' is
upgraded first. For an explanation of types please refer to lxcu-createsh(1).
OPTIONS
-d, --dist 'distribution-name'

-h, --help Display this help information

-n, --name 'container name'

-r, --rel 'release-name'

-t, --type 'type-name' e.g. basic or dev.....

-V, --version Print script version information
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success

1 - General failure

64 - Error in command line
FILES
lxcu.conf  The script reads the configuration file to set default values.
